RetailPulse – E-commerce Analytics Pipeline

RetailPulse is an end-to-end analytics project that demonstrates a complete data workflow:
data generation, database loading, star schema modeling, and business intelligence dashboarding.

The project simulates an e-commerce sales environment and shows how raw transactional data can be
transformed into actionable insights using Python, SQL Server, and Power BI.

It was designed as a portfolio project for Data Analyst / BI Developer roles.

a) Project Overview
RetailPulse implements a simplified analytics pipeline for an online retail business.

The workflow includes:

1.Generating synthetic e-commerce sales data in Python
2.Loading raw transactional data into SQL Server
3.Building analytical views for key business metrics
4.Creating a star schema data model
5.Building an interactive Power BI dashboard

The result is a complete end-to-end analytics solution.

b) Architecture

Python Data Generation
        ↓
SQL Server (RAW tables)
        ↓
SQL KPI Views
        ↓
Star Schema Model
        ↓
Power BI Dashboard

Pipeline components:
Python scripts → SQL database → Analytical views → Power BI dashboard

