e) Data Model

The analytical model follows a star schema design.

Fact table:
fact_sales

Dimensions:
dim_date
dim_product

Relationships:
dim_date → fact_sales
dim_product → fact_sales

This structure allows efficient aggregation and filtering in Power BI.

f) Key Metrics

The dashboard includes several business metrics commonly used in e-commerce analytics.

Total Revenue
Total sales revenue generated by all orders.
SUM(fact_sales.revenue)

Revenue YTD (Year-to-Date)
Total revenue accumulated since the beginning of the year.
TOTALYTD([Revenue], dim_date[order_date])

Average Order Value (AOV)
Average value of a customer order.
Revenue / Number of Orders

Product Revenue Share
Percentage contribution of each product to total revenue.
Revenue of Product / Total Revenue

g) Dashboard Features

The Power BI dashboard provides interactive analysis including:

• Daily revenue trend
• Top 10 products by revenue
• Revenue share by product
• Average order value
• Revenue YTD
• Interactive date filtering

The dashboard allows quick identification of:

•top performing products
•revenue trends
•sales distribution

